# devkit dogfoods its OWN gate-engine. The bins are local (this IS the devkit repo), so the
# gates run via `node gate-engine/...` rather than the published `bunx guard-*`.

# Formatter + linter (Biome) — hard gate.
bun run lint || exit 1

# Structure governance (folder-structure rule compiled from guard.config.json `structure`) — hard
# gate. devkit governs its own cli/ + gate-engine/ layout; an unregistered domain or misplaced file
# blocks the commit. See docs/structure-governance.md.
bun run lint:structure || exit 1

# Ratchets (baselines in eslint/baselines/, grandfathered via `bun run guard:freeze`) — hard gate.
node gate-engine/ratchets/folder-fanout.mjs gate || exit 1
node gate-engine/ratchets/size-disable.mjs gate || exit 1

# fallow audit (dead-code + complexity + duplication on the changed set) — advisory (fail-open):
# surfaces findings, never blocks; no-ops when the fallow CLI is not installed.
command -v fallow >/dev/null 2>&1 && fallow audit || true
